{
  "text": "Neurobehavioral effects of HIV in rural China demographically corrected norms). In the United States, a number of studies have found increased rates of NP impairment in asymptomatic HIV' groups. In a review of the latter studies, [CITATION_1] reported a median of 31% NP impairment prevalence among medically asymptomatic HIV' groups; this is consistent with the 29% prevalence rate that we observed in the non-AIDS FPDs in China.",
